  "prompt": "How can I recover deleted photos from app lock new version?",
  "response": "Recovering deleted photos from an app that uses App Lock can be challenging, especially if the app doesn't provide a built-in recovery feature. However, here are a few general steps you might consider:\n\n1. **Check App Features:**\n   - Open the app and navigate through its settings or help section to see if there is a recovery or backup feature. Some apps might save a copy or have a \"recently deleted\" option where you can restore items within a certain time frame.\n\n2. **Use Cloud Backup:**\n   - If your device is set up with a cloud service (like Google Photos for Android or iCloud for iOS), check there. These services often back up photos automatically, even if they were deleted from the local storage.\n\n3. **Look in the Archive or Trash:**\n   - If you're using a photo gallery app with archiving or trash features, check those areas. Photos are sometimes moved there before permanent deletion.\n\n4. **Third-party Recovery Software:**\n   - If the above steps don't work, you can try using data recovery software. There are several tools available (like Recuva, DiskDigger, or EaseUS MobiSaver) that might recover deleted files from your device\u2019s storage.\n   - Be cautious and research thoroughly before downloading any third-party software to ensure it's reputable and safe.\n\n5. **Professional Data Recovery Services:**\n   - If the photos are particularly important and you\u2019ve been unsuccessful with other methods, consider consulting with a professional data recovery service. They have specialized tools and expertise to recover deleted files, although this can be expensive.\n\n6. **Regular Backup:**\n   - Moving forward, regularly back up important photos and data to an external drive or cloud service to prevent future data loss.\n\nRemember that the success of recovering deleted photos greatly depends on how the data is managed after deletion and whether new data has overwritten it.",
